<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CFD55F9F96005F99B" authority="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin, 2017" authorityName="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin" authorityYear="2017" box="[306,515,1589,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pusillopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polulus" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CFD55F9F96005F99B" box="[306,515,1589,1613]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Pusillopagurus polulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D5794FF97457CFE6CF9F96090F99A" box="[523,662,1589,1613]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by present designation. Gender: masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3406576FF97457CFCE3F94463FBF926" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE536FDFF97457CFCE3F94463FBF926" blockId="36.[131,776,1672,1776]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
ETYMOLOGY. — The generic name is a combination of the genus name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CFCA5F96F630BF96C" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[194,269,1699,1722]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CFCA5F96F630BF96C" box="[194,269,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Pagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CFDCAF96E63F5F96C" authorityName="Forest &amp; de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1968" box="[429,499,1698,1722]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Nematopaguroides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CFDCAF96E63F5F96C" box="[429,499,1698,1722]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which refers to something very small, and used in reference to the minuscule size of specimens in the single species of this new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3406576FF97457CFCE3F8DC63FEF894" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE536FDFF97457CFCE3F8DC63FEF894" blockId="36.[132,774,1808,1858]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
DISTRIBUTION. — Known based on the 
<typeStatus id="54E1885FFF97457CFE4DF8DC6050F8FE" box="[554,598,1808,1832]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">type</typeStatus>
species found in 
<collectingCountry id="F34D766DFF97457CFCE1F8E662DDF894" box="[134,219,1834,1858]" name="Curaçao" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Curaçao</collectingCountry>
, at a depth of 
<quantity id="4CA29B18FF97457CFD0FF8E663F2F894" box="[360,500,1834,1858]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="11.58" metricValueMin="1.52" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" unit="m" value="65.5" valueMax="115.8" valueMin="15.2">15.2-115.8 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3406576FF97457CFCE3F8A561F7FB94" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE536FDFF97457CFCE3F8A561F7FB94" blockId="36.[130,776,1896,2026]" lastBlockId="36.[811,1457,828,1090]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">DIAGNOSIS. — Eight pairs of biserial phyllobranch gills, only 1 pleurobranch on somite XII (thoracomere 7, above pereopod 4). Rostrum triangular. Ischium edge of crista dentata projected medially, lacking accessory tooth. Chelipeds subequal in length, somewhat slender. Sternite of somite XI (thoracomere 6, pereopod 3) with anterior lobe subrectangular, bilobed. Pereopod 4 with single row of scales on propodal rasp, dactyl lacking preungual process. Pereopod 5 semi-chelate. Male with coxae of pereopods 5 symmetrical, with paired, unequal sexual tubes, right tube much longer than left, distally coiled and filamentous, left tube not coiled or filamentous; with unpaired, left pleopods 3-5. Female with paired gonopores, and unpaired, left pleopods 2-5. Telson nearly symmetrical, longer than broad, with lateral indentations dividing anterior and posterior lobes; terminal margins of posterior lobes weakly oblique, armed with distinct spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3406576FF97457CFF4AFBB966B2F95A" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE536FDFF97457CFF4AFBB96197FB5B" blockId="36.[811,1457,1141,1676]" box="[813,913,1141,1167]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE536FDFF97457CFF4AFB5866B2F95A" blockId="36.[811,1457,1141,1676]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
There are no clear morphological similarities between this new genus and other known pagurid genera in which the male has sexual tubes, despite some having similar sexual tubes. As in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CFF4AFB3F61C4FADB" authority="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin, 2017" authorityName="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin" authorityYear="2017" box="[813,962,1267,1293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pusillopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CFF4AFB3F61C4FADB" box="[813,962,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Pusillopagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D5794FF97457CFFAFFB386614FAD8" box="[968,1042,1268,1294]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and at least 18 other pagurid genera in which the male has paired sexual tubes, the right is longer than the left. In general morphology, the tubes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CF97FFAFF67ABFA9B" authority="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin, 2017" authorityName="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin" authorityYear="2017" box="[1304,1453,1331,1357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pusillopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CF97FFAFF67ABFA9B" box="[1304,1453,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Pusillopagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D5794FF97457CFF4AFA98617FFAB8" box="[813,889,1364,1390]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CF8DDFA9F61CFFA5B" authority="de Saint Laurent, 1968" authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1968" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Trichopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CF8DDFA9F674BFABB" box="[1210,1357,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Trichopagurus</emphasis>
de Saint Laurent, 1968
</taxonomicName>
(described in more detail in de Saint Laurent [1970b]), and to a lesser extent those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CF89DFA5F6605FA1B" authority="McLaughlin, 1997" authorityName="McLaughlin" authorityYear="1997" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Alainopaguroides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CF89DFA5F67B6FA7B" box="[1274,1456,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Alainopaguroides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B0CFF97457CFF4AFA7F6605FA1B" author="MCLAUGHLIN P. A." box="[813,1027,1459,1485]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" pagination="433 - 572" refId="ref25463" refString="MCLAUGHLIN P. A. 1997. - Crustacea Decapoda: Hermit crabs of the family Paguridae from the KARUBAR cruise in Indonesia, in CROSNIER A. &amp; BOUCHET P. (eds), Resultats des Campagnes MUSOR- STOM volume 16. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris: 433 - 572 (Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle; 172)." type="book chapter" year="1997">McLaughlin, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CF826FA7F67ADFA1B" authority="McLaughlin, 1997" authorityName="McLaughlin" authorityYear="1997" box="[1089,1451,1459,1485]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Icelopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CF826FA7F66C1FA1B" box="[1089,1223,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Icelopagurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B0CFF97457CF8B6FA7F67ADFA1B" author="MCLAUGHLIN P. A." box="[1233,1451,1459,1485]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" pagination="433 - 572" refId="ref25463" refString="MCLAUGHLIN P. A. 1997. - Crustacea Decapoda: Hermit crabs of the family Paguridae from the KARUBAR cruise in Indonesia, in CROSNIER A. &amp; BOUCHET P. (eds), Resultats des Campagnes MUSOR- STOM volume 16. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris: 433 - 572 (Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle; 172)." type="book chapter" year="1997">McLaughlin, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in most other important morphological features, such as the cephalic shield and appendages, third maxilliped crista dentata, chelipeds, ambulatory legs, and telson, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D7EFF97457CF914F9DE6196F99A" authority="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin, 2017" authorityName="Lemaitre &amp; Felder &amp; Poupin" authorityYear="2017" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pusillopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B92EEAEFFF97457CF914F9DE6196F99A" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Pusillopagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D5794FF97457CFFFFF9FF61E3F99B" box="[920,997,1587,1613]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs markedly from these three genera. Furthermore, the number of gills in this new genus is eight, whereas it is 
<quantity id="4CA29B18FF97457CFFD1F9BE61E9F95A" box="[950,1007,1650,1676]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
those other three.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
